<chapter title="License" file="License">

<cite>Launcher</cite> is <strong>Freeware</strong>.  Copyright is held by the author, Stephen Fryatt, 2003.

<cite>Launcher</cite> may be copied freely, so long as it remains unaltered with all its files and documentation intact.  All copies should have their <file>Choices</file> file (if present) deleted from within the application to ensure that new users receive <cite>Launcher</cite> in its default state.

If you wish to distribute <cite>Launcher</cite>, please contact me to get my permission. This is so that I can ensure that you have the latest version available. <cite>Launcher</cite> may not be sold, although Public Domain libraries may charge for the cost of discs.

No guarantee is made as to the suitability or stability of <cite>Launcher</cite> for any particular purpose.  No liability can be accepted by the author for any problems or damage caused by the use of <cite>Launcher</cite>.

</chapter>




<chapter title="Introduction" file="Introduction">

<cite>Launcher</cite> is yet another application launcher for RISC OS, which sits to the side of the desktop and allows applications to be started from a palette of shortcuts.

</chapter>




<chapter title="Installing Launcher" file="Installation">

<cite>Launcher</cite> requires RISC OS 3.1 or later.  It can be run off a hard disc or floppy disc.

To install <cite>Locate</cite> on a hard disc, copy the <file>!Launcher</file> application to a suitable directory.

</chapter>




<chapter title="Using Launcher" file="Use">

To use <cite>Launcher</cite>, run it in the usual way by double-clicking on its icon. It will install itself on the desktop, placing a bar down the left-hand side of the screen.

</chapter>




<chapter title="Configuration" file="Configuration">

Selecting <menu>Choices...</menu> from the main menu allows the default behaviour of <cite>Launcher</cite> to be changed.

</chapter>




<chapter title="Version History" file="History">

This is a complete list of all the changes made to the publicly released versions of <cite>Launcher</cite>.

<subhead title="0.30 (18 December 2004)">

<list>
<li>Initial unreleased version.
</list>


<subhead title="0.40 (--------)">

<list>
<li>Refactored for modular style and updated to handle new SFLib APIs.
<li>Rebuilt for ARMv7 systems, and the opportunity taken to restructure the code and tidy aspects of the user interface.
</list>


</chapter>




<chapter title="Future Plans" file="ToDo">

This version of <cite>Launcher</cite> is still not finished and several intended features are not yet implemented.

</chapter>





